content: That's really helpful, thanks! I think I need to work on prioritizing my tasks better and eliminating non-essential tasks. I've been feeling overwhelmed with the transition to my new role and trying to take on too much at once. I'm going to start using the Eisenhower Matrix and the ABCD method to prioritize my tasks and focus on high-leverage activities. Do you have any advice on how to handle meetings and emails, which seem to be taking up a lot of my time?
